      • remove

        public void remove(AppliedSkillLevelRepository rep,
                   SkillLevelRepository myRep,
                   SkillLevel refactor)
        Removes the given SkillLevel and refactors all applications that contain it to one specific SkillLevel.
        Parameters:
        rep - The AppliedSkillLevelRepository so that the applications can save themselves after updating the skill level they are hooked up to.
        myRep - The SkillLevelRepository so that this SkillLevel can delete itself.
        refactor - The SkillLevel to be used to replace this one in all applications

      • remove

        public void remove(AppliedSkillLevelRepository rep,
                   SkillLevelRepository myRep,
                   SkillLevel refactorUp,
                   SkillLevel refactorDown)
        Removes the given SkillLevel and refactors all applications that contain it either upwards or downwards.
        Parameters:
        rep - The AppliedSkillLevelRepository so that the applications can save themselves after updating the skill level they are hooked up to.
        myRep - The SkillLevelRepository so that this SkillLevel can delete itself.
        refactorUp - The SkillLevel to be used to replace this one in applications that are refactored up to a new SkillLevel
        refactorDown - The SkillLevel to be used to replace this one in applications that are refactored down to a new SkillLevel
